## Errors & Mistakes
- The partial commit printed `codex_config.toml: needs merge` on stderr.
  This was NOT an error â€” it is git's informational notice that the real
  index contains unmerged entries, which git skipped because a partial
  commit builds its tree from HEAD + the pathspec only. The commit
  succeeded (exit 0). Pi confirmed via `git show` / `git diff --name-only
  HEAD~1 HEAD` that the commit contained ONLY `AGENTS_global.md`.
- Pi was initially uncertain whether the unmerged `codex_config.toml`
  entries would block a partial commit (`git commit -- <pathspec>`).
  Reasoning that resolved it: the "cannot do a partial commit during a
  merge" guard fires only when `whence != FROM_COMMIT` (i.e., a MERGE_HEAD
  exists). Here no MERGE_HEAD existed, so the guard did not fire, and the
  partial commit's HEAD-based tree write was unaffected by the unmerged
  entries living in the real index. Confirmed empirically by the
  successful commit.
- No file contents were modified. No files other than AGENTS_global.md
  were staged or committed.

